data.title: Google Photos: Edit, Organize, Search, and Backup Your Photos
data.meta_description: Edit and enhance photos with AI-powered features like Magic Editor and Magic Eraser on Google Photos. Store, organize & search your memories.
data.text:
GoogleÂ Photos never sells your photos, videos, or personal information to anyone, and we don't use your photos and videos for advertising.

Every Google Account comes with 15 GB of storage for GoogleÂ Photos, Gmail, and Google Drive. You can also buy more storage with a Google One membership plan.

Yes, GoogleÂ Photos works on both iOS and Android devices. Get the app to get started. You can also use it on Desktop and Tablet devices. Learn more about how GoogleÂ Photos integrates with your deviceâs default gallery.

You can automatically save your photos and videos to your Google Account when you turn on backup. You can enable backup while setting up your Photos app or if you go to the Settings page and turn backup on. You can also manually backup your photos. Learn more about the benefits of backup.

To edit photos on your mobile device, download and install the GoogleÂ Photos app. Some editing features including Magic Eraser, Photo Unblur, and Magic Editor are only available in the GoogleÂ Photos app. Learn more about how to edit your photos and videos.

You can search your photos for anything. For example, you can search by places youâve traveled, your pet, your best friend, foods and more. To more easily search and manage your photos, you can apply a name to people or pets that appear in your photos. Learn more about Face Groups and how to search your photos.
